<div class="fn-group p font-secondary-light font-sm">
<div class="fn p" id="FN2"><p id="P30">This retrospective study, utilizing data from the Sight Outcomes Research Collaborative (SOURCE) involving 67,517 patients, found that only 0.87% developed uveitis within three months of starting topical glaucoma medications, with significantly lower incidence rates and odds of uveitis observed among users of prostaglandin analogues compared to other medication classes.</p></div>
